               <head>Selections in Persian translation of the universal history, the Akhbār al-rusul va al-mulūk</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Akhbār al-rusul va al-mulūk</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh87000556 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85067895" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_753-item1">
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Untitled collection of select episodes from a Persian translation, possibly the version translated in 352 by 
                <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_45495483" role="aut">Abū ʿAlī Muḥammad Balʿamī</persName>(d. 363/973), based on the universal history, the 
                <title key="work_21727">Akhbār al-rusul va al-mulūk</title>, by 
                <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_9854001" role="aut">Abū Jaʿfar Muḥammad ibn Jarīr al-Ṭabarī</persName>(d. 310/923).
                        </p>
                        <p>Rubrication.</p>
                        <p>Additional clarifications of subject matter in margins.</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end.</p>
                        <p>Neat scribal nastaʿlīq.</p>
                        <p>Annotations.</p>
                        <p>Loose folded paper wrapper (ledger, probably from an Acquittance Roll, dated April 1828, Calcutta), upper and lower parts missing, watermarked (J Whatman, UEIC 1825, Balston &amp; Co.); torn, stained, and incomplete.</p>
                     </note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
